						<summary>

						<p>On the west wall of the central shrine in the Chōḷēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Sundarapāṇḍya: Śaka. 1293, Virōdhi (for Virōdhikṛit), Tai 3 = 1311 A.D., December 29 (Wednesday). The Śaka year was probably a mistake for 1233.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription records the gift of a bowl, bell, incense-burner and lamp to god Rājēndraśōḷīśvaram-uḍaiyanāyanār at Poṉṉamarāpati in Puṟamalaināḍu by Vīranārāyaṇa ••• ••• <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Iṉbavaṉapperumāḷ for the merit of the king.</p>						

						<p>Cf. Inscriptions (Texts) of the Pudukkottai State, No. 778 (for 773 ?).</p>						

						</summary>
